During the seminars different drama texts are analysed, applying various
methods and approaches. Students write short plays or dramatize prose text and give each other feedback. The final essay is an independent analysis of 1-2 theatre texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Learning to analyze theatre texts, including conventional drama and postdramatic theatre texts. Acquaire basic dramatization or playwriting skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students  - know drama poetics and basic features of postdramatic text,  - are able to apply relevant methods of analysis,  - are able analyse all different parts of a theatre text and a theatre text as a whole,  - have acquired basic level writing skills for a short play or dramatization of a prose text - recognizes the stage potential of a theatre text.
